title: Monteverdi - Madrigali erotici - Rooley, Consort of Musicke
description:
Monteverdi: Madrigali erotici.

Most of these madrigals come from Claudio Monteverdi's seventh book of madrigals, from 1619, written when he was working in Venice. They are scored for two, three, or four voices with instrumental accompaniment. As you might imagine, their common theme is love.

The performers are as follows:

Emma Kirkby, Judith Nelson, Poppy Holden - sopranos
Paul Elliott, Andrew King - tenors
Richard Wistreich - baritone
David Thomas - bass

The Consort of Musicke, directed by Anthony Rooley

Please enjoy.
